Cryptic strategies in 
<taxonomicName id="4C254D2AFFCD481AFDC0F8F1FD5CAC55" authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1838" box="[535,680,1841,1863]" class="Insecta" family="Acanthopidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mantodea" pageId="2" pageNumber="333" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Acanthopidae</taxonomicName>
: 1, 
<taxonomicName id="4C254D2AFFCD481AFD1AF8F1FCE2AC55" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1877" box="[717,790,1841,1863]" class="Insecta" family="Acanthopidae" genus="Metilia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mantodea" pageId="2" pageNumber="333" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B951EABBFFCD481AFD1AF8F1FCE2AC55" box="[717,790,1841,1863]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="333">Metilia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp., a male with partially decaying, dry-leaf habitus (specimen from Novo Airão, Amazonas State, Brazil—Photo by Antonio Agudelo); 2: 
<taxonomicName id="4C254D2AFFCD481AFC75F890FC1FAC74" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1877" box="[930,1003,1872,1894]" class="Insecta" family="Acanthopidae" genus="Metilia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mantodea" pageId="2" pageNumber="333" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B951EABBFFCD481AFC75F890FC1FAC74" box="[930,1003,1872,1894]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="333">Metilia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
